        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-02T21:45:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is intended to be used during init() time (e.g. in an func init() {...} or to initialize global variable).\n\n  var mintTokenPerm \u003d realms.RegisterPermission(\"luci.serviceAccounts.mintToken\")\n\n  func checkPermission(...) {\n    ... mintTokenPerm\n  }\n\nCalling it all the time is wasteful (why would we want keep registering same permission over and over again?).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 53,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 53,
        "endChar": 61
      },
      "revId": "4a11b793d1c9476e64a3302beb3d471c80301265",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0a7215ba_28ae6913",
        "filename": "casviewer/handlers.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 53,
      "author": {
        "id": 1366072
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-03T06:57:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I thought we have \"NewPermission\" in realms package, but there isn\u0027t. \nAnd couldn\u0027t make a Permission because `name` isn\u0027t exposed.\nAnd found this one saying.\n\n```\nRegisterPermission ... or returns an existing one.\n```\n\nhttps://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/luci-go/+/master/server/auth/realms/permissions.go\n\nBut looking at the code, this takes mutex lock. \nSo should be called in each request, indeed.\n\nWould it make sense to have `NewPermission`? like\n\n\n  NewPermission(name string) (Permission, error) {\n    if err :\u003d ValidatePermissionName(name); err !\u003d nil {\n      return nil, err\n    }\n    return Permission{name: name}\n  }",
      "parentUuid": "d167a45d_b60ff8ac",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 53,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 53,
        "endChar": 61
      },
      "revId": "4a11b793d1c9476e64a3302beb3d471c80301265",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
